{
  "text": "Several mechanisms linking visceral fat accumulation to endothelial dysfunction and atherosclerosis have been postulated: alterations in adipocytokines, lipids, insulin resistance, inflammation and oxidative stress [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Although the pathophysiology of visceral adiposity has been extensively studied in conditions such as MetS or type 2 diabetes, there have been few studies on healthy Japanese subjects whose VFA values are below the criterion [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . As a preventive measure, health-promoting actions should be taken before serious cardiovascular events occur. For this purpose, it is important to understand the underlying mechanisms connecting visceral fat accumulation and progression of atherosclerosis in Japanese adults. Moreover, not only the roles of classical risk factors (high blood pressure, glucose intolerance and dyslipidemia) but also those of other markers (adipocytokines and inflammation) for arteriosclerotic vascular diseases should be clarified.",
  "correct_citation": {
